metadata.name: Villagers way
metadata.description:
image title of villagers way

 This piece conveys the feeling of  Thai identity
 In the water there are fish, in the fields there is rice.  Refers to fertile land  People do not starve dry mouth.  It is comparable to that in every body of water there are fish for food and in the fields there is abundant rice.  This expression is often used when talking about our country.
 The reason why the expression is often used in water with fish, in rice fields when talking about our country is because our country is an agricultural country.  abundant  both in the cultivation of plants and animal husbandry  It can produce enough food for domestic consumption and the remainder is exported to foreign countries as well.  We can say that our country is the world's breadbasket.
